## 7. Figures for all new analyses (`R/viz_*.R`, `scripts/run_all_figures.R`)

### Why
This adds a ggplot2 figure layer covering all of them.

### Design principles (from the dataviz guidance)
- **Color assigned by the data's job**: sequential viridis for magnitude, a blue-grey-red **diverging** scale centered at 0 for signed quantities (log2 odds ratios, correlations), Okabe-Ito categorical (fixed order, ≤8) for methods/regions. All three are colorblind-safe by construction.
- **The ~46 cell types are never color-encoded** (no palette survives that many categories) — they always sit on an axis (heatmaps, facets, sorted bars).
- Shared theme + palette helpers live in `R/viz_theme.R`; every figure is saved as both PDF and PNG.

### Changes
- **`R/viz_theme.R`** (new): `okabe_ito_palette()`, `theme_analysis()`, `scale_fill_diverging()`/`scale_color_diverging()`, `scale_fill_magnitude()`, `save_figure()`.
- **`R/viz_spatial_stats.R`** (new): contrast effect-size heatmap (region × cell-type × contrast, significance-starred), per-contrast forest plots with CIs, region-heterogeneity interaction bar, co-occurrence correlation heatmap, and an optional co-occurrence network (guarded by igraph/ggraph).
- **`R/viz_pathway.R`** (new): per-cell-type GSEA dot plot (NES) and ranked-gene volcano.
